# STMS Project Rules

Support Ticket Management System — full-stack MERN app (`client/` + `server/`).

## Architecture

- **Server:** Express → validators → controllers → Mongoose models; business logic in `server/src/utils/`
- **Client:** pages → `TicketContext` (useReducer) → `client/src/services/api.js` → `/api` proxy
- **Docs:** `api-contract.md`, `design-notes.md`, `acceptance-criteria.md`, `ai-prompts/`

## Critical Business Rule — Status Workflow

Status transitions are enforced **server-side** in `server/src/utils/statusTransitions.js`:

```
Open → In Progress, Cancelled
In Progress → Resolved, Cancelled
Resolved → Closed
Closed, Cancelled → terminal (no transitions)
```

- Status changes **only** via `PATCH /api/tickets/:id/status`
- `PUT /api/tickets/:id` must **reject** status field changes
- Mirror allowed transitions in `client/src/utils/constants.js` for UI buttons
- Any workflow change requires updates to utility, constants, tests, and `api-contract.md`

## Backend Conventions

- Thin controllers: `async/await`, delegate to utils, use `next(error)` — no inline `res.status()` for errors
- Validation: `express-validator` in `server/src/middleware/validators.js`; use `.optional({ checkFalsy: true })` for optional query params
- Errors: `AppError` + global `errorHandler`; response shape `{ success: false, message: "..." }`
- Success: `{ success: true, data: ... }`; lists include `pagination`
- Populate `createdBy` and `assignedTo` on ticket responses
- Cascade delete comments on ticket delete (`Comment.deleteMany`)
- Swagger JSDoc on routes in `server/src/routes/`

## Frontend Conventions

- All HTTP via `client/src/services/api.js` — no raw `fetch` or duplicate Axios instances
- Use `cleanParams()` before GET requests (strip empty `status`, `search`, etc.)
- State: React Context + `useReducer` only — no Redux/Zustand
- Reuse components: `Layout`, `Badge`, `Alert`, `Spinner`, `TicketForm`, `TicketFilters`
- Every page: loading (`Spinner`), empty state, success/error (`Alert`)
- `baseURL: '/api'` — never hardcode `http://localhost:5000` in components

## MVP Scope

- **No authentication** — users are seed data; `createdBy` from request body
- Do not add auth, rate limiting, or new frameworks unless explicitly requested

## Testing & Verification

- Server changes: add/update integration tests in `server/tests/`; run `cd server && npm test`
- Test behavior (HTTP status + body), not internals; use `mongodb-memory-server`
- Status workflow changes: cover all valid and invalid transitions
- Client changes: run `cd client && npm run build` for large UI changes

## Change Discipline

- Minimal diff — solve the task, no unrelated refactors or cleanup
- No new dependencies unless necessary; justify and pin versions
- No secrets in code, tests, or docs; use `.env` (never commit `.env`)
- Follow existing naming: `ticketController.js`, `ticketRoutes.js`, etc.

## Git

- Branch: `cursor/<ticket>-<summary>` — never push directly to `main`
- Commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `test:`, `docs:` prefixes

## Anti-Patterns

```javascript
// ❌ Change status via PUT
PUT /api/tickets/:id { status: "Closed" }

// ✅ Dedicated status endpoint
PATCH /api/tickets/:id/status { status: "Closed" }

// ❌ Axios in a page component
axios.get('http://localhost:5000/api/tickets')

// ✅ API service layer
import { getTickets } from '../services/api';
```
